
[1]congregate

   CONGREGATE, v.t. [L., a herd. See Gregarious.] To collect separate
   persons or things into an assemblage; to assemble; to bring into one
   place, or into a crowd or united body; as, to congregate men or
   animals; to congregate waters or sands.

   CONGREGATE, v.i. To come together; to assemble; to meet.

   Equals with equals often congregate.

          CONGREGATE, a. Collected; compact; close. [Little used.]
